parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trunk/tailgate latch mechanism can cause the trunk/tailgate to open unexpectedly while driving, leading to accidents or loss of cargo. Additionally, the inability to open the trunk/tailgate from the inside can leave occupants stranded.
symptoms: The trunk/tailgate will not unlock or open
the trunk/tailgate latch does not catch
the trunk/tailgate opens unexpectedly while driving
the trunk/tailgate must be held shut with a cord or other means.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding door latch can cause the doors to open unexpectedly while driving, leading to accidents or loss of cargo. Additionally, the inability to open or close the sliding doors can leave occupants stranded.
symptoms: The sliding doors will not latch or open
the sliding doors open unexpectedly while driving
the sliding doors must be held shut with a cord or other means.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Valve Body Shift Solenoid Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the transmission valve body shift solenoid can cause the engine to overheat, potentially leading to engine damage or failure, which can result in costly repairs or even a vehicle fire.
symptoms: Engine overheating
transmission malfunction
unusual engine behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or near-misses.
symptoms: Cruise control does not disengage
vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
ABS/ESC lights illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the parking brake or transmission system can cause the vehicle to roll forward or move unexpectedly when parked, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle rolls forward when parked on an incline
difficulty shifting into gear
unusual transmission behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake stop lamp switch can cause the rear brake lights to remain illuminated even when the vehicle is turned off, which can lead to confusion and potential accidents.
symptoms: The rear brake lights stay on even when the vehicle is turned off
the "ESC" light is illuminated
the vehicle gets stuck in park
intermittent brake light failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause the cruise control to cease functioning, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control independently ceases functioning
the cruise control switch is illuminated but the cruise function will not engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design flaw in the headlight circuit can cause the low beam headlights to be very dim, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The low beam headlights are very dim
the small yellow front marker light (194 bulb) has burned out
limited lighting when on low beam.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
the brake pedal is depressed but fails to stop the vehicle
the engine revs or fails to respond to the gas pedal
the vehicle slows down naturally and eventually comes to a stop
the issue recurs after restarting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the electronic throttle control can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and increase the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal stops working
the engine does not respond to the gas pedal
the vehicle slows down naturally and eventually comes to a stop
the issue recurs after restarting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal is depressed but fails to stop the vehicle
the emergency brakes fail
the vehicle crashes into an object.
